hoose the best VPN for Windows?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_q_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_q_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="dtc-text-base font-sans rich-text"><p>The Proton VPN app for Windows has been specifically engineered to be secure, fast, and easy to use. You can use Proton VPN to stream your favorite shows, share files over BitTorrent, access censored content and protect your privacy. Proton VPN is a community-supported VPN service and our mission is to create an internet where privacy is the default. Founded by CERN scientists to ensure everyone can protect their right to privacy, Proton VPN offers one of the only free VPN services with no data limits, no logs, and no privacy-invading ads.</p></div></div></dd></div><div role="listitem" class="[&amp;:nth-child(n+2)]:border-t border-gray-400/30 py-4"><dt role="term" class="relative flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-6 text-start"><div class="flex-grow"><div class="font-semibold"><div class="dtc-text-lg text-purple-800 font-sans rich-text">How to install a VPN on Windows?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_1a_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_1a_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="font-sans rich-text"><p><a href="/pricing">Sign up for</a> a Proton VPN account, <a href="#hero">download</a> our Windows app, and double click the downloaded file to start installation. A wizard will guide you through the rest of the process.</p></div></div></dd></div><div role="listitem" class="[&amp;:nth-child(n+2)]:border-t border-gray-400/30 py-4"><dt role="term" class="relative flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-6 text-start"><div class="flex-grow"><div class="font-semibold"><div class="dtc-text-lg text-purple-800 font-sans rich-text">How to easily connect to a VPN server on Windows?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_1q_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_1q_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="dtc-text-base font-sans rich-text"><p>If you sign in to the app and click &quot;Quick Connect&quot;, Proton VPN will automatically connect you to the fastest server depending on your location. It&#x27;s that easy. If you&#x27;re on a paid plan, you can also manually connect to a server in a particular country or a specialized server (for example, a Tor-enabled server).</p></div></div></dd></div><div role="listitem" class="[&amp;:nth-child(n+2)]:border-t border-gray-400/30 py-4"><dt role="term" class="relative flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-6 text-start"><div class="flex-grow"><div class="font-semibold"><div class="dtc-text-lg text-purple-800 font-sans rich-text">How to access blocked content with a VPN on Windows?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_2a_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_2a_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="font-sans rich-text"><p>You can use the Proton VPN Windows app to access content that has been blocked by your internet service provider, government, workplace, or college. To access it, simply connect to a VPN server in an area where that content is not censored. If you have a VPN Plus or Proton Unlimited account, you can also access popular streaming services by connecting to a Plus server.</p></div></div></dd></div><div role="listitem" class="[&amp;:nth-child(n+2)]:border-t border-gray-400/30 py-4"><dt role="term" class="relative flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-6 text-start"><div class="flex-grow"><div class="font-semibold"><div class="dtc-text-lg text-purple-800 font-sans rich-text">What is the fastest VPN for Windows?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_2q_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_2q_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="font-sans rich-text"><p>Proton VPN operates over 20,000 servers in more than 140 countries around the world, so there will always be a VPN server nearby to provide you with a secure, fast connection. Users with a VPN Plus or Proton Unlimited plan can access our large and expanding network of high-speed 10 Gbps Plus servers.</p><p>The &quot;Quick Connect&quot; feature in our Windows app automatically chooses the fastest server available for your location. You can also use the server load information shown next to each server&#x27;s name to help you manually select the fastest server for your needs.</p></div></div></dd></div><div role="listitem" class="[&amp;:nth-child(n+2)]:border-t border-gray-400/30 py-4"><dt role="term" class="relative flex w-full items-center justify-start gap-6 text-start"><div class="flex-grow"><div class="font-semibold"><div class="dtc-text-lg text-purple-800 font-sans rich-text">How do I know if my processor is x64, ARM64 or x86 (32-bit)?</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="def-_r67R_3a_" class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full text-center font-semibold outline-none transition-[color,background-color,border-color,box-shadow] duration-150 ease-out motion-reduce:transition-none text-purple-500 ring-purple-800 ring-offset-white hocus:bg-purple-700 hocus:text-white bg-transparent no-underline ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring  p-3 before:absolute before:inset-0" title="View details"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md w-6 h-6 [&amp;_svg]:h-full [&amp;_svg]:w-full"><!--$--><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" data-testid="dynamic-hero-icon"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg><!--/$--></div><span class="sr-only">View details</span></button></div></dt><dd role="definition" id="def-_r67R_3a_" aria-hidden="true" class="hidden"><div class="mt-4 animate-enter-top-fade space-y-4"><div class="dtc-text-base font-sans rich-text"><p>To find out if your Windows computer uses an x64, ARM64 or x86 (32-bit) processor:</p><ol><li>Open the <strong>System Information</strong> tool. To do this, press <strong>Win + R</strong> to open the <strong>Run</strong> dialog (&quot;Win&quot; is the key with the Windows logo), type msinfo32 , and click <strong>Enter</strong>. Alternatively, search for <strong>System Information</strong> from the <strong>Start</strong> menu.</li><li>Go to <strong>System Summary</strong> → <strong>System Type</strong>. Your system architecture will be listed here.</li></ol></div></div></dd></div></dl></div></div></div><!--astro:end--></astro-island> </main> <link rel="preload" as="image" href="https://vpncdn.protonweb.com/image-transformation/?s=c&amp;image=image%2Fupload%2Fv1776940263%2Fstatic%2Flogos%2Fvpn%2Fvpn-trademark-b2c-light.svg"/><footer class="pt-4 md:pt-8 xl:pt-12 pb-4 md:pb-8 xl:pb-12 px-4 md:px-8 xl:px-16"><div class="max-w-9xl mx-auto"><div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-12" data-testid="footer"><div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-12 md:gap-4 xl:gap-6"><div class="col-span